Press Release<br /><!-- NewsDate.start -->March 10, 2006<!-- NewsDate.end --><p style="text-align: center">
<span class="PRTitle"><!-- NewsTitle.start -->VILLAR: FIRE PROTECTION CAMPAIGNS SHOULD 
BE INTENSIFIED<!-- NewsTitle.end --></span><br /><span class="PRSub"><!-- NewsTitleSub.start -->The public should cooperate in the 
campaign to avoid fire incidents this summer<!-- NewsTitleSub.end--></span></p>
<!-- NewsBody.start --><p align="justify" style="text-indent: 25px">Senator 
Manny Villar, Chairman of the Senate Committee on Public Order, urges the Bureau 
of Fire Protection (BFP) to intensify its fire prevention campaign. At the same 
time, Villar encourages the public to fully cooperate in various fire-prevention 
programs to avoid fire incidents from occurring this summer.</p>
<p align="justify" style="text-indent: 25px">&quot;As we celebrate Fire Prevention 
Month this month, all of us should join hands in ensuring that we will be safe. 
We all know the tremendous damage that fire brings to not only properties but to 
the lives and the safety of people as well. Thus, we should work together 
towards fire prevention,&quot; says Villar, President of the Nacionalista Party.</p>
<p align="justify" style="text-indent: 25px">Based on figures from BFP, there 
were 10,728 fire incidents last year that resulted in the death of 249 people, 
injuries to 661 people and damages to properties worth around P3.27 billion.</p>
<p align="justify" style="text-indent: 25px">&quot;These figures are really alarming 
considering the number of families that have been left homeless or lost a family 
member. We hope these would dramatically decrease this year. Although as of the 
first week of March this year, there were already 1,672 fire incidents reported 
that resulted to damages worth over P250,000,&quot; adds Villar.         </p>
<p align="justify" style="text-indent: 25px">The theme for this 
year's Fire Prevention Month celebration of BFP is 'Pamayanan Sama-Sama Laban sa 
Sunog'. Activities such as conduct of industrial and commercial fire drill 
exercises, conduct of lectures about fire safety, the organization of fire 
disaster control brigades in barangay among others.         </p>
<p align="justify" style="text-indent: 25px">Villar further cites, &quot;We should be 
more vigilant towards fire prevention and protection during the summer period 
because it is when most fire incidents are reported. We should take all 
necessary precautions especially in monitoring and checking electric 
installations in our houses and building. Even our children should learn about 
fire safety tips.&quot;</p>
